hwL2VpnPwe3.name: hwL2VpnPwe3

revisions.description: Modify the description of hwSvcForBfdIndex,hwSvcDelayTime, hwSvcReroutePolicy, hwSvcRerouteReason, hwSvcLastRerouteTime.
The max length of hwPWVcQosProfile,hwPWVcSwitchQosProfile, hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcQosProfile, hwSvcQosProfile, hwPWTemplateQosProfile changed from 31 to 63.
Add OBJECT(hwL2vpnTnlType, hwL2vpnTunnelIndex) to SVC MIB Trap(hwSvcDown); Add OBJECT(hwL2vpnTnlType, hwL2vpnTunnelIndex) to PWE3 MIB Trap(hwPWVcDown).
Add OBJECT(hwSvcActive) to SVC MIB Trap(hwSvcDown,hwSvcUp); Add OBJECT(hwPWVcActive) to PWE3 MIB Trap(hwPWVcDown,hwPWVcUp,hwPWVcBackup).

hwL2VpnPwe3.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwL2VpnPwe3.description: The HUAWEI-PWE3-MIB contains objects to manage PWE3.

HWLdpPwStateChangeReason.name: HWLdpPwStateChangeReason
HWLdpPwStateChangeReason.description: The type indicates the reason of LDP PW VC's status change: LDP session down (1) AC interface down (2) PSN tunnel state down (3) Mapping message not received (4) PW interface parameter not match (5) Notification not forwarding (6)

hwPWVcTable.name: hwPWVcTable
hwPWVcTable.description: This table is the VC configuration table. Users can create or delete a VC by it.

hwPWVcEntry.name: hwPWVcEntry
hwPWVcEntry.description: Provides the information of a VC entry.

hwPWVcID.name: hwPWVcID
hwPWVcID.description: Index for the conceptual row identifying a PW within this PW Emulation table.Used in the outgoing PW ID field within the 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element'.

hwPWVcType.name: hwPWVcType
hwPWVcType.description: The type of the Virtual Circuit.This value indicate the service to be carried over this PW.

hwPWVcPeerAddrType.name: hwPWVcPeerAddrType
hwPWVcPeerAddrType.description: Denotes the address type of the peer node. It should be set to 'unknown' if PE/PW maintenance protocol is not used and the address is unknown. Currently, support 'ipv4' only.

hwPWVcPeerAddr.name: hwPWVcPeerAddr
hwPWVcPeerAddr.description: This object contain the value of the peer node address of the PW/PE maintenance protocol entity. This object SHOULD contain a value of all zeroes if not applicable (hwPWVcPeerAddrType is 'unknown').

hwPWVcStatus.name: hwPWVcStatus
hwPWVcStatus.description: Indicates the status of the PW in the local node. Currently, can't support 'plugout'.

hwPWVcInboundLabel.name: hwPWVcInboundLabel
hwPWVcInboundLabel.description: For ldp vc, the value will be created by system automatically.

hwPWVcOutboundLabel.name: hwPWVcOutboundLabel
hwPWVcOutboundLabel.description: For ldp vc, the value will be created by system automatically.

hwPWVcSwitchID.name: hwPWVcSwitchID
hwPWVcSwitchID.description: Used in the outgoing PW ID field within the 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element' of the switch PW.

hwPWVcSwitchPeerAddrType.name: hwPWVcSwitchPeerAddrType
hwPWVcSwitchPeerAddrType.description: Denotes the address type of the peer node of the switch PW. It should be set to 'unknown' if PE/PW maintenance protocol is not used and the address is unknown. Currently, support 'ipv4' only.

hwPWVcSwitchPeerAddr.name: hwPWVcSwitchPeerAddr
hwPWVcSwitchPeerAddr.description: This object contain the value of the peer node address of the switch PW of the PW/PE maintenance protocol entity. This object SHOULD contain a value of all zeroes if not applicable (hwPWVcSwitchPeerAddrType is 'unknown').

hwPWVcSwitchInboundLabel.name: hwPWVcSwitchInboundLabel
hwPWVcSwitchInboundLabel.description: For ldp vc, the value will be created by system automatically.

hwPWVcSwitchOutboundLabel.name: hwPWVcSwitchOutboundLabel
hwPWVcSwitchOutboundLabel.description: For ldp vc, the value will be created by system automatically.

hwPWVcGroupID.name: hwPWVcGroupID
hwPWVcGroupID.description: Used in the Group ID field sent to the peer PWES within the maintenance protocol used for PW setup. Applicable if pwVcOwner equal 'pwIdFecSignaling' or 'l2tpControlProtocol', should be set to zero otherwise. Currently, this value always be zero.

hwPWVcIfIndex.name: hwPWVcIfIndex
hwPWVcIfIndex.description: Index of the interface (or the virtual interface) associated with the PW.

hwPWVcAcStatus.name: hwPWVcAcStatus
hwPWVcAcStatus.description: Local AC status. Currently, can't support 'plugout'.

hwPWVcACOAMStatus.name: hwPWVcACOAMStatus
hwPWVcACOAMStatus.description: Denotes the AC's protocol is operational or not.

hwPWVcMtu.name: hwPWVcMtu
hwPWVcMtu.description: If not equal zero, the optional Mtu object in the signaling protocol will be sent with this value, representing the locally supported MTU size over the interface (or the virtual interface) associated with the PW.

hwPWVcCtrlWord.name: hwPWVcCtrlWord
hwPWVcCtrlWord.description: If signaling is used for PW establishment, this object indicates the status of the control word negotiation, and in both signaling or manual configuration indicates if CW is to be present or not for this PW.

hwPWVcVCCV.name: hwPWVcVCCV
hwPWVcVCCV.description: Indicates the optional VCCV capabilities of the PW. According to whether the control word is enabled, the value can be ccCw(0)|ccAlert(1)|ccTtl(6)|cvLspping(4)|cvBfd(5) or ccAlert(1)|ccTtl(6)|cvLspping(4)|cvBfd(5). The default value is ccAlert(1)|ccTtl(6)|cvLspping(4)|cvBfd(5).

hwPWVcBandWidth.name: hwPWVcBandWidth
hwPWVcBandWidth.description: This object indicates the bandwidth. '0' is the default value.

hwPWVcMaxAtmCells.name: hwPWVcMaxAtmCells
hwPWVcMaxAtmCells.description: Indicates the max cell supported when vc type is atm.

hwPWVcTnlPolicyName.name: hwPWVcTnlPolicyName
hwPWVcTnlPolicyName.description: Indicates the tunnel policy name used.

hwPWVcQoSBehaviorIndex.name: hwPWVcQoSBehaviorIndex
hwPWVcQoSBehaviorIndex.description: Indicates the traffic behavior Index when QOS is implemented. Currently,can't support.Return the default value is '0'.

hwPWVcExplicitPathName.name: hwPWVcExplicitPathName
hwPWVcExplicitPathName.description: Indicates the explicit path name set by the operator.Currently, can't support.

hwPWVcTemplateName.name: hwPWVcTemplateName
hwPWVcTemplateName.description: Indicates the PW template index referenced.

hwPWVcSecondary.name: hwPWVcSecondary
hwPWVcSecondary.description: Indicates whether or not the secondary PW is used.

hwPWVcUpTime.name: hwPWVcUpTime
hwPWVcUpTime.description: Indicates the duration when the PW keeps Up for the last time, in seconds.

hwPWOAMSync.name: hwPWOAMSync
hwPWOAMSync.description: Denotes the AC and PSN are enable or not.

hwPWVCForBfdIndex.name: hwPWVCForBfdIndex
hwPWVCForBfdIndex.description: The index of PW for BFD.

hwPWVcManualSetFault.name: hwPWVcManualSetFault
hwPWVcManualSetFault.description: Denotes the manual has been set fault or not.

hwPWVcActive.name: hwPWVcActive
hwPWVcActive.description: Denotes the current vc is active or not.

hwPWVcVrIfIndex.name: hwPWVcVrIfIndex
hwPWVcVrIfIndex.description: Denotes the VRRP interface this PW binding to.

hwPWVcVrID.name: hwPWVcVrID
hwPWVcVrID.description: Denotes the VrID this PW binding to.

hwPWBFDMinReceiveInterval.name: hwPWBFDMinReceiveInterval
hwPWBFDMinReceiveInterval.description: The interval of bfd messages to be received.

hwPWBFDMinTransmitInterval.name: hwPWBFDMinTransmitInterval
hwPWBFDMinTransmitInterval.description: The interval of bfd messages to be sent.

hwPWDynamicBFDDetect.name: hwPWDynamicBFDDetect
hwPWDynamicBFDDetect.description: This value indicates the capacitability to support dynamic BFD detect.

hwPWBFDRemoteVcID.name: hwPWBFDRemoteVcID
hwPWBFDRemoteVcID.description: In the multiple-hop model, the value of remote VC id.

hwPWEthOamType.name: hwPWEthOamType
hwPWEthOamType.description: This value indicates the type of ETH OAM.

hwPWCfmMaIndex.name: hwPWCfmMaIndex
hwPWCfmMaIndex.description: This value indicates the current CFM MA index.

hwPWVcUpStartTime.name: hwPWVcUpStartTime
hwPWVcUpStartTime.description: Specifies the time this PW status was Up(1).

hwPWVcUpSumTime.name: hwPWVcUpSumTime
hwPWVcUpSumTime.description: Indicates the accumulated time when the VC is Up, in seconds.

hwPWVcIfName.name: hwPWVcIfName
hwPWVcIfName.description: Name of the interface (or the virtual interface) associated with the PW.

hwPWVcRowStatus.name: hwPWVcRowStatus
hwPWVcRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this Table. Restriction: The row must be created by 'createAndGo' handle only. Handle 'createAndWait' is forbidden. Not support modifying configuration.

hwPWVcSwitchTnlPolicyName.name: hwPWVcSwitchTnlPolicyName
hwPWVcSwitchTnlPolicyName.description: Indicates the switch tunnel policy name used.

hwPWVcCfmMdIndex.name: hwPWVcCfmMdIndex
hwPWVcCfmMdIndex.description: This value indicates the current CFM MD index.

hwPWVcCfmMaName.name: hwPWVcCfmMaName
hwPWVcCfmMaName.description: This value indicates the current CFM MA name used.

hwPWVcCfmMdName.name: hwPWVcCfmMdName
hwPWVcCfmMdName.description: This value indicates the current CFM MD name used.

hwPWVcRawOrTagged.name: hwPWVcRawOrTagged
hwPWVcRawOrTagged.description: Specifies whether the raw or tagged is configured.

hwPWVcInterworkingType.name: hwPWVcInterworkingType
hwPWVcInterworkingType.description: Specifies the interworking type of the VC entry.

hwPWVcCir.name: hwPWVcCir
hwPWVcCir.description: Specifies the committed information rate, based on the VC entry.

hwPWVcPir.name: hwPWVcPir
hwPWVcPir.description: Specifies the peak information rate, based on the VC entry.

hwPWVcQosProfile.name: hwPWVcQosProfile
hwPWVcQosProfile.description: Specifies the QoS profile's name, based on the VC entry.

hwPWVcSwitchCir.name: hwPWVcSwitchCir
hwPWVcSwitchCir.description: Specifies the committed information rate, based on the switch VC entry.

hwPWVcSwitchPir.name: hwPWVcSwitchPir
hwPWVcSwitchPir.description: Specifies the peak information rate, based on the switch VC entry.

hwPWVcSwitchQosProfile.name: hwPWVcSwitchQosProfile
hwPWVcSwitchQosProfile.description: Specifies the QoS profile's name, based on the switch VC entry.

hwPWVcTrigger.name: hwPWVcTrigger
hwPWVcTrigger.description: Specifies whether the PW remote interface shutdown or not.

hwPWVcEnableACOAM.name: hwPWVcEnableACOAM
hwPWVcEnableACOAM.description: Specifies whether ACOAM detection and notification are all enabled or not.

hwPWVcSwitchVrIfIndex.name: hwPWVcSwitchVrIfIndex
hwPWVcSwitchVrIfIndex.description: Denotes the VRRP interface the switch PW binding to.

hwPWVcSwitchVrID.name: hwPWVcSwitchVrID
hwPWVcSwitchVrID.description: Denotes the VrID the switch PW binding to.

hwPWVcQosParaFromPWT.name: hwPWVcQosParaFromPWT
hwPWVcQosParaFromPWT.description: This object indicates the configuration of the Qos parameters managed through command line or PW template.

hwPWVcBfdParaFromPWT.name: hwPWVcBfdParaFromPWT
hwPWVcBfdParaFromPWT.description: This object indicates the configuration of the Bfd parameters managed through command line or PW template.

hwPwVcNegotiateMode.name: hwPwVcNegotiateMode
hwPwVcNegotiateMode.description: This object indicates the negotiation mode of the PW on the local node.

hwPwVcIsBypass.name: hwPwVcIsBypass
hwPwVcIsBypass.description: This object indicates whether the PW is the bypass PW.

hwPwVcIsAdmin.name: hwPwVcIsAdmin
hwPwVcIsAdmin.description: This object indicates whether the PW is the administrator PW.

hwPwVcAdminPwIfIndex.name: hwPwVcAdminPwIfIndex
hwPwVcAdminPwIfIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the interface on which the administrator PW resides after it is being tracked by the service PW.

hwPwVcAdminPwLinkStatus.name: hwPwVcAdminPwLinkStatus
hwPwVcAdminPwLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the status of the administrator PW after it is being tracked by the service PW.

hwPwVcSwitchAdminPwIfIndex.name: hwPwVcSwitchAdminPwIfIndex
hwPwVcSwitchAdminPwIfIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the interface on which the administrator PW resides after it is being tracked by the switch PW.

hwPwVcSwitchAdminPwLinkStatus.name: hwPwVcSwitchAdminPwLinkStatus
hwPwVcSwitchAdminPwLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the status of the administrator PW after it is being tracked by the switch PW.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupAdminPwIfIndex.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupAdminPwIfIndex
hwPwVcSwitchBackupAdminPwIfIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the interface on which the administrator PW resides after it is being tracked by the switch backup PW.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupAdminPwLinkStatus.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupAdminPwLinkStatus
hwPwVcSwitchBackupAdminPwLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the status of the administrator PW after it is being tracked by the switch backup PW.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcId.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcId
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcId.description: This object indicates the VC ID of the switch backup PW.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPeerAddrType.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPeerAddrType
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPeerAddrType.description: This object indicates type of the IP address of the peer on the switch backup PW. Currently, only IPv4 addresss are supported.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPeerAddr.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPeerAddr
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPeerAddr.description: This object indicates the IP address of the peer on the switch backup PW.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcReceiveLabel.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcReceiveLabel
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcReceiveLabel.description: This object indicates the inbound label of the switch backup VC. For a static VC, the value of the inbound label ranges from 16 to 1023. For a dynamic VC, the inbound label is automatically generated by the system.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcSendLabel.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcSendLabel
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcSendLabel.description: This object indicates the outbound label of the switch backup VC. For a static VC, the value of the outbound label ranges from 0 to 1048575. For a dynamic VC, the outbound label is automatically generated by the system.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcTnlPolicyName.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcTnlPolicyName
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcTnlPolicyName.description: This object indicates the name of the tunnel policy of the switch backup VC.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcCir.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcCir
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcCir.description: This object indicates the CIR of the switch backup VC.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPir.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPir
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcPir.description: This object indicates the PIR of the switch backup VC.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcQosProfile.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcQosProfile
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcQosProfile.description: This object indicates the name of the QoS profile of the switch backup VC.

hwPwVcSlaveMasterMode.name: hwPwVcSlaveMasterMode
hwPwVcSlaveMasterMode.description: This object indicates whether the status of the VC is master or slave.

hwPwVcSwitchVcSlaveMasterMode.name: hwPwVcSwitchVcSlaveMasterMode
hwPwVcSwitchVcSlaveMasterMode.description: This object indicates whether the status of the switch VC is master or slave.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcSlaveMasterMode.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcSlaveMasterMode
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcSlaveMasterMode.description: This object indicates whether the status of the switch backup VC is master or slave.

hwPwVcSwitchVcActive.name: hwPwVcSwitchVcActive
hwPwVcSwitchVcActive.description: This object indicates whether the status of the switch VC is active or not.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcActive.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcActive
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcActive.description: This object indicates whether the status of the switch backup VC is active or not.

hwPwVcSwitchCwTrans.name: hwPwVcSwitchCwTrans
hwPwVcSwitchCwTrans.description: This object indicates whether the SPE support Control Word Transparent or not,default is false.

hwPwVcSwitchVcServiceName.name: hwPwVcSwitchVcServiceName
hwPwVcSwitchVcServiceName.description: This object indicates the service name of the switch VC.

hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcServiceName.name: hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcServiceName
hwPwVcSwitchBackupVcServiceName.description: This object indicates the service name of the switch backup VC.

hwPWVcTnlTable.name: hwPWVcTnlTable
hwPWVcTnlTable.description: This table is used to search the tunnel index of a VC.

hwPWVcTnlEntry.name: hwPWVcTnlEntry
hwPWVcTnlEntry.description: Provides the information of a VC tunnel entry.

hwPWVcTnlIndex.name: hwPWVcTnlIndex
hwPWVcTnlIndex.description: This object indicates the tunnel index of the VC.

hwPWVcTnlType.name: hwPWVcTnlType
hwPWVcTnlType.description: This object indicates the tunnel type.

hwPWTnlForBfdIndex.name: hwPWTnlForBfdIndex
hwPWTnlForBfdIndex.description: This object indicates the index of LSP for BFD.

hwPWVcStatisticsTable.name: hwPWVcStatisticsTable
hwPWVcStatisticsTable.description: This table contains the Pwe3's VC packets statistics.

hwPWVcStatisticsEntry.name: hwPWVcStatisticsEntry
hwPWVcStatisticsEntry.description: Provides the information of the Pwe3's VC packets statistics.

hwPWVcStatisticsRcvPkts.name: hwPWVcStatisticsRcvPkts
hwPWVcStatisticsRcvPkts.description: The total number of packets received on this VC.

hwPWVcStatisticsRcvBytes.name: hwPWVcStatisticsRcvBytes
hwPWVcStatisticsRcvBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on this VC.

hwPWVcStatisticsSndPkts.name: hwPWVcStatisticsSndPkts
hwPWVcStatisticsSndPkts.description: The total number of packets sent on this VC.

hwPWVcStatisticsSndBytes.name: hwPWVcStatisticsSndBytes
hwPWVcStatisticsSndBytes.description: The total number of bytes sent on the VC.

hwPWRemoteVcTable.name: hwPWRemoteVcTable
hwPWRemoteVcTable.description: This table provides remote PW information for each local PW.

hwPWRemoteVcEntry.name: hwPWRemoteVcEntry
hwPWRemoteVcEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by the agent for every PW.

hwPWRemoteVcID.name: hwPWRemoteVcID
hwPWRemoteVcID.description: Used in the outgoing PW ID field within the 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element' of the remote PW.

hwPWRemoteVcType.name: hwPWRemoteVcType
hwPWRemoteVcType.description: This value indicate the service to be carried over the remote PW.

hwPWRemoteVcStatus.name: hwPWRemoteVcStatus
hwPWRemoteVcStatus.description: Indicates the forwarding status of the remote VC.

hwPWRemoteVcGroupID.name: hwPWRemoteVcGroupID
hwPWRemoteVcGroupID.description: Indicates the Group ID field of the remote PW. Currently, this value always be zero.

hwPWRemoteVcMtu.name: hwPWRemoteVcMtu
hwPWRemoteVcMtu.description: Indicates the supported MTU size of the remote PW.

hwPWRemoteVcCtrlword.name: hwPWRemoteVcCtrlword
hwPWRemoteVcCtrlword.description: Indicates the control word capability of the remote PW.

hwPWRemoteVcMaxAtmCells.name: hwPWRemoteVcMaxAtmCells
hwPWRemoteVcMaxAtmCells.description: Indicates the max cell supported of the remote PW when vctype is atm.

hwPWRemoteVcNotif.name: hwPWRemoteVcNotif
hwPWRemoteVcNotif.description: Indicates notification is supported by the remote PW.

hwPWVcSwitchNotifEnable.name: hwPWVcSwitchNotifEnable
hwPWVcSwitchNotifEnable.description: If this object is set to enable(1), then it enables the emission of hwPWVcSwitchWtoP and hwPWVcSwitchPtoW notifications; otherwise these notifications are not emitted. The default value is disable (2).

hwPWVcUpDownNotifEnable.name: hwPWVcUpDownNotifEnable
hwPWVcUpDownNotifEnable.description: This object indicates the enable sign of PW VC state change notification. The default value is disable (2).

hwPWVcDeletedNotifEnable.name: hwPWVcDeletedNotifEnable
hwPWVcDeletedNotifEnable.description: This object indicates the enable sign of PW VC deletion notification. The default value is disable (2).

hwPWVcStateChangeReason.name: hwPWVcStateChangeReason
hwPWVcStateChangeReason.description: This object indicates the reason of PE VC state change.

hwPWVcSwitchRmtID.name: hwPWVcSwitchRmtID
hwPWVcSwitchRmtID.description: This object indicates the VC ID of PW switch between working PW and protect PW .

hwLdpPWStateChangeReason.name: hwLdpPWStateChangeReason
hwLdpPWStateChangeReason.description: This object indicates the reason of LDP PW VC's state change.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentTable.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentTable
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentTable.description: This table provides per TDM PW performance information. The contents of this table entry are reset to zero and gotten new information every 15 minutes.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentEntry.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentEntry
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by the agent for every TDM PW entry.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMissingPkts.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMissingPkts
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMissingPkts.description: Number of missing packets (as detected via control word sequence number gaps).

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrOverruns.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrOverruns
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrOverruns.description: Number of times the jitter buffer was overrun.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrUnderruns.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrUnderruns
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentJtrBfrUnderruns.description: Number of times a packet needed to be played out and the jitter buffer was empty.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMisOrderDropped.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMisOrderDropped
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMisOrderDropped.description: Number of packets detected out of order (via control word sequence numbers) that could not be re-ordered or could not fit in the jitter buffer.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMalformedPkt.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMalformedPkt
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentMalformedPkt.description: Number of packets detected with unexpected size or bad headers' stack.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentESs.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentESs
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentESs.description: The counter associated with the number of Error Seconds encountered. Any malformed packet, sequence error, LOPS, and the like are considered as Error Seconds.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentSESs.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentSESs
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentSESs.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Error Seconds encountered.

hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentUASs.name: hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentUASs
hwPWVcTDMPerfCurrentUASs.description: The counter associated with the number of Unavailable Seconds encountered. Any consecutive ten seconds of SES are counted as one Unavailable Seconds (UAS).

hwPWVcSwitchWtoP.name: hwPWVcSwitchWtoP
hwPWVcSwitchWtoP.description: This notification is generated when switch from working PW to protect PW happens.

hwPWVcSwitchPtoW.name: hwPWVcSwitchPtoW
hwPWVcSwitchPtoW.description: This notification is generated when switch from protect PW to working PW happens.

hwPWVcDown.name: hwPWVcDown
hwPWVcDown.description: This notification indicates the VC's state changes to down.

hwPWVcUp.name: hwPWVcUp
hwPWVcUp.description: This notification indicates the VC's state changes to up.

hwPWVcDeleted.name: hwPWVcDeleted
hwPWVcDeleted.description: This notification indicates the VC is deleted.

hwPWVcBackup.name: hwPWVcBackup
hwPWVcBackup.description: This notification indicates the VC's state changes to backup.

hwLdpPWVcDown.name: hwLdpPWVcDown
hwLdpPWVcDown.description: This notification indicates the LDP PW VC's state changes to down.

hwLdpPWVcUp.name: hwLdpPWVcUp
hwLdpPWVcUp.description: This notification indicates the Ldp PW VC's state changes to up.

hwPWVcStatusChange.name: hwPWVcStatusChange
hwPWVcStatusChange.description: This notification indicates the VC's Active state changed.

hwVpwsPwRedundancyDegraded.name: hwVpwsPwRedundancyDegraded
hwVpwsPwRedundancyDegraded.description: VPWS PW redundancy reported a protect degraded alarm.

hwVpwsPwRedundancyDegradedClear.name: hwVpwsPwRedundancyDegradedClear
hwVpwsPwRedundancyDegradedClear.description: VPWS PW redundancy reported the clearing of the protect degraded alarm.

hwSvcTable.name: hwSvcTable
hwSvcTable.description: This table is the SVC configuration table. Users can create or delete a SVC by it.

hwSvcEntry.name: hwSvcEntry
hwSvcEntry.description: Provides the information of a SVC entry.

hwSvcIfIndex.name: hwSvcIfIndex
hwSvcIfIndex.description: Index of the interface (or the virtual interface) associated with the PW.

hwSvcID.name: hwSvcID
hwSvcID.description: Index for the conceptual row identifying a PW within this PW Emulation table.Used in the outgoing PW ID field within the 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element'.

hwSvcType.name: hwSvcType
hwSvcType.description: Index for the conceptual row identifying a PW within this PW Emulation table.This value indicate the service to be carried over this PW.

hwSvcPeerAddrType.name: hwSvcPeerAddrType
hwSvcPeerAddrType.description: Denotes the address type of the peer node. It should be set to 'unknown' if PE/PW maintenance protocol is not used and the address is unknown. Currently, support 'ipv4' only.

hwSvcPeerAddr.name: hwSvcPeerAddr
hwSvcPeerAddr.description: This object contain the value of the peer node address of the PW/PE maintenance protocol entity. This object SHOULD contain a value of all zeroes if not applicable (hwSvcPeerAddrType is 'unknown').

hwSvcStatus.name: hwSvcStatus
hwSvcStatus.description: Indicates the status of the PW in the local node. Currently, can't support 'plugout'.

hwSvcInboundLabel.name: hwSvcInboundLabel
hwSvcInboundLabel.description: This object indicates the inbound label.

hwSvcOutboundLabel.name: hwSvcOutboundLabel
hwSvcOutboundLabel.description: This object indicates the outbound label.

hwSvcGroupID.name: hwSvcGroupID

hwPWTemplateTable.name: hwPWTemplateTable
hwPWTemplateTable.description: This table specifies information for configuring and status monitoring to PW tempalte.

hwPWTemplateEntry.name: hwPWTemplateEntry
hwPWTemplateEntry.description: A row in this table represents a pseudo wire (PW) template. It is indexed by hwPWCmdTemplateIndex, which uniquely identifying a singular tempalte.

hwPWTemplateName.name: hwPWTemplateName
hwPWTemplateName.description: The name of the PW template. Set by the operator to indicate the protocol responsible for establishing this PW. The value 'static' is used in all cases where no maintenance protocol (PW signaling) is used to set-up the PW, i.e. require configuration of entries in the PW tables including PW labels, etc. The value 'ldp' is used in case of signaling with the PWid FEC element with LDP signaling. The value 'rsvp' indicate the use of rsvp control protocol.

hwPWTemplatePeerAddrType.name: hwPWTemplatePeerAddrType
hwPWTemplatePeerAddrType.description: Denotes the address type of the peer node. It should be set to 'unknown' if PE/PW maintenance protocol is not used and the address is unknown. Currently, support 'ipv4' only.

hwPWTemplateVCCV.name: hwPWTemplateVCCV
hwPWTemplateVCCV.description: Indicates the optional VCCV capabilities of the PW template. According to whether the control word is enabled, the value can be ccCw(0)|ccAlert(1)|ccTtl(6)|cvLspping(4)|cvBfd(5) or ccAlert(1)|ccTtl(6)|cvLspping(4)|cvBfd(5). The default value is ccAlert(1)|ccTtl(6)|cvLspping(4)|cvBfd(5).
